Hooli Announces Fourth Quarter and Fiscal Year 2021 Results

    MOUNTAIN VIEW, Calif. – February 1, 2022 – Hooli Inc. (NASDAQ: HOOL, HOOLI) today announced
financial results for the quarter and fiscal year ended December 31, 2021.

Gavin Belson, CEO of Hooli, said: “Our deep investment in AI technologies continues to drive
extraordinary and helpful experiences for people and businesses, across our most important products. Q4 saw
ongoing strong growth in our advertising business, which helped millions of businesses thrive and find new
customers, a quarterly sales record for our Pixel phones despite supply constraints, and our Cloud business
continuing to grow strongly.”

Patrice Alexander, CEO of Hooli, said: “Our fourth quarter revenues of $75 billion, up 32% year over year,
reflected broad-based strength in advertiser spend and strong consumer online activity, as well as substantial
ongoing revenue growth from Google Cloud. Our investments have helped us drive this growth by delivering the
services that people, our partners and businesses need, and we continue to invest in long-term opportunities.”

Hooli Inc., a company listed on NASDAQ under the ticker symbol HOOL/HOOLI, has released its financial results for the fourth quarter and full fiscal year ending December 31, 2021. The announcement was made by Gavin Belson, Chief Executive Officer (CEO), who emphasized the success of their investment in artificial intelligence (AI) technologies, leading to positive outcomes for both consumers and businesses through improved experiences with Hooli's key products.

In the fourth quarter, Hooli experienced significant growth in various areas:

1. Advertising Business: Strong demand led to robust growth in the advertising sector, helping numerous businesses expand their customer base and achieve greater success.

2. Pixel Phones Sales: Despite facing supply constraints, Hooli achieved a quarterly sales record for its Pixel phone lineup, demonstrating continued market traction.

3. Google Cloud Revenue: The company's investments in Google Cloud contributed to sustained revenue growth during the period.

For the entire fiscal year 2021, Hooli reported consolidated revenues of $75 billion, marking an increase of 32% compared to the previous year. This growth can be attributed to increased advertiser spending, heightened consumer online activity, and consistent expansion of the Google Cloud segment.

Overall, Hooli's leadership team credits these achievements to the quality of services they provide and their commitment to long-term investments that meet the needs of customers, partners, and businesses alike.
